HEADWORD: craseur
<hw>⟦Eacute⟧`cra`seur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧craser</ets> to crush.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>An
instrument intended to replace the knife in many operations, the parts
operated on being severed by the crushing effect produced by the gradual
tightening of a steel chain, so that hemorrhage rarely
follows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

